President Barack Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama released a statement on the passing of Muhammad Ali, describing him as "The Greatest." They expressed their gratitude for having known him and highlighted his impact on the world. The statement mentioned a pair of Ali's gloves displayed in the president's study, symbolizing his greatness. It also discussed Ali's journey from being Cassius Clay to embracing the Muslim faith and his activism for civil rights. The statement acknowledged that Ali was not perfect but praised his infectious spirit and his later work for peace and reconciliation. It concluded by stating that Ali shook up the world and that the world is better for it. The Obamas offered their condolences to Ali's family and wished for him to rest in peace.